<br>
I strongly suggest you go and see your local congressman and Representative.  Most major areas have a suboffice where you can make an appointment.  A letter from one of those guys tends to get any Federal worker, Ie VA Hospital Administrator , doctor, ect feet moving because their jobs depend on it.<br>
<br>
This is provided that he was honorably discharged ect.<br>
<br>
It may be unconfortable going and seeing him/ her but it will get you done what is needed. I have seen so many problems cured with one such letter in my 10 yrs of military service that it would amaze you. Most people dont realize the power a Congressman has over the military. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=487635">Swyftfeet Librettist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
